text: Nihel Ghoul (born 2 June 1984) is a Tunisian national volleyball player. She played at the 2014 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship. She graduated from University of Rouen. She played for Olympic Club of Kelibia, UGS Havre Ocean / HAC, CEP Poitiers Saint-Benoît, and Volley-ball Saint-Dié-des-Vosges. == References == Category:1984 births Category:Living people Category:Tunisian volleyball players
